The Palestinian President Mahmud Abbas announced at the UN General Assembly on Thursday that he would break all agreements with Israel if the future government of the country tried to fulfill Benjamin Netanyahu's announcement of the annexation of occupied Palestinian lands.
"If the future government of Israel, which will arise, will proceed to the implementation of this plan, we will cancel all signed agreements (with Israel) and withdraw from all commitments made," he said.
