For even easier operation of headphones, a quick silence button is placed on the microphone, and the HyperSense performance regulator and the balance slider between the game and the cabin are placed on the headphone housing.
Self-adapting to the shape of the headband ensures a smooth and accurate fit.
In addition, Razer Nari Ultimate for Xbox One features Xbox Wireless, which allows you to directly connect to a console without the need to use a wireless receiver, allowing you to easily and quickly configure.
Headphones also support Windows Sonic, which provides a more realistic sound.
Razer Nari Ultimate, originally designed for PCs, debuted on the market in September 2018.
