According to the newspaper, disregarding a certain order of conduct issued by a police officer is to be a new kind of offense, threatened by a fine, arrest or restriction of liberty.
The police union wants to make a change like this.
The idea went to the Committee on Petitions.
"The case is serious, because already every year more than half a million criminal cases are brought to Polish courts," we read.
The "Rzeczpospolita" has determined that the petition that the Independent Trade Union of Police has written to Members on the revision of the Code of Offence has a chance of success.
The petitioners shall propose a new wording of Article 54a of the Code of Offence.
It would read, "Whoever is not subject to a request or order from a public officer, issued within the limits and under the provisions of the law, is subject to arrest, fines or restrictions of liberty."
“Paragraph 3 of this provision refers to the same punishment for those who do not execute orders, do not make it impossible or difficult to carry out their duties,” states the journal.
